:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:666:\"<p>Want to track your Formidable Forms conversions to see which forms are most loved on your site? With Google Analytics, you can track your forms conversions, but it’s got quite a learning curve for beginners. Fortunately, there’re smart tools like MonsterInsights to help you set up forms tracking and other advanced events trackings easily in [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-formidable-forms-conversions-with-google-analytics/\">How to Track Formidable Forms Conversions with Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12645:\"<p>Want to track your Formidable Forms conversions to see which forms are most loved on your site? With Google Analytics, you can track your forms conversions, but it’s got quite a learning curve for beginners. Fortunately, there’re smart tools like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> to help you set up forms tracking and other advanced events trackings easily in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to track your Formidable Forms conversions with Google Analytics the easy way: using MonsterInsights.</p>\n<h3>Setting Up Formidable Forms Tracking in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/formidable-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Formidable Forms</a> is the most advanced WordPress form builder plugin available on the market. The plugin lets you create advanced forms like quizzes, surveys, payment forms, registration forms, directories, job board listings, etc. easily. It’s one of the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\">best form builder plugins for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>You can set up Formidable Forms tracking with Google Analytics in 2 ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>By Setting Up Event Goals in Google Analytics – The Manual Way</li>\n<li>By Using MonsterInsights – The Automatic (Easy) Way</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you choose the first method, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-goal-in-google-analytics-to-track-conversions/\">set up event goals in Google Analytics&#8217;</a> interface and define your form conversions as event goals. This method is the far less user-friendly approach. If you aren’t a developer, it’ll take a lot of your time and effort to learn, or take a lot of your money to hire a developer.</p>\n<p>Whereas the second method is speedy and effortless. It takes just a few steps to set up forms tracking in Google Analytics using MonsterInsights. All you need to do to set up forms tracking is to install the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\">MonsterInsights Forms addon</a> in your WordPress dashboard. Then, MonsterInsights handles the rest automatically.</p>\n<h3>Benefits of Using MonsterInsights vs. Manual Setup to Track Forms</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157422\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It simplifies the entire process of using Google Analytics on your WordPress site. It comes with a set of simple-yet-powerful <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/features/\">addons</a>, like the Forms addon, to allow you track advanced metrics easily.</p>\n<p>There’re many benefits of using MonsterInsights&#8217; Forms addon versus setting up forms tracking manually in Google Analytics&#8217; interface. Below are just a few key benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Easy and quick setup</strong>: You can set up forms tracking on your site easily, in just a few minutes. You’d need to spend a lot of time and energy or hire a developer to set up forms tracking otherwise.</li>\n<li><strong>Set up and view reports within your WordPress dashboard</strong>: You can set up forms tracking and view your forms reports within your WordPress dashboard. Hence, you can keep working on your site while viewing your Analytics reports &#8211; you don’t need to navigate away from your site.</li>\n<li><strong>Most comprehensive reports</strong>: MonsterInsights provides you with most comprehensive reports for all your website metrics. Your forms conversion reports in MonsterInsights are way more simple and easy to understand than in the Google Analytics platform itself.</li>\n<li><strong>Works with your favorite form builder</strong>: Alongside Formidable Forms, MonsterInsights supports all the major WordPress form builder plugins including <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPForms</a> and <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/ninja-forms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Ninja Forms</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Clearly, using MonsterInsights Forms addon is the best option for tracking Formidable Forms conversions. You can buy <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">MonsterInsights Pro</a> to enjoy this feature.</p>\n<h3>How to Track Formidable Forms Conversions Using MonsterInsights</h3>\n<p>First, install the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">MonsterInsights plugin</a> on your WordPress site and <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">set up Google Analytics using the plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>After that, navigate to <strong>Insights » Addons</strong> from your WordPress dashboard and find <strong>Forms Addon</strong>. Then, click the <strong>Install</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-104951\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon.jpg\" alt=\"install mi forms addon\" width=\"381\" height=\"478\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon.jpg 381w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon-239x300.jpg 239w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 381px) 100vw, 381px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll see the button change to the <strong>Activate</strong> option. Simply click the button to activate the addon.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-104952\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon-activate.jpg\" alt=\"forms addon activate\" width=\"382\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon-activate.jpg 382w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/forms-addon-activate-240x300.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 382px) 100vw, 382px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you&#8217;ll see the addon&#8217;s status as <strong>active</strong>.</p>\n<p>That’s it! You have completed the setup process in literally 2 clicks!</p>\n<p>You don’t need any further configuration.</p>\n<p>Now, the plugin will automatically start tracking your Formidable Forms conversions. Normally, Google Analytics takes 24 to 48 hours to track events like form conversions, so you can check your reports after the given time.</p>\n<p>Now, let’s go ahead and learn how to view your form conversion reports.</p>\n<h3>How to View Formidable Forms Conversion Reports</h3>\n<p>With <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights Forms</a>, you can view all your important website data right in your WordPress dashboard without having to open another website. Yes, that’s right! You can view your forms conversion reports inside your dashboard as well.</p>\n<p>To view your forms reports, go to <strong>Insights » Reports</strong> from your WordPress dashboard. There, you&#8217;ll see the <strong>Overview Report</strong> of your entire site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157435\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-overview-report\" width=\"620\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report-300x278.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>To view your form reports, click the <strong>Forms</strong> link.</p>\n<p>Then, you&#8217;ll see your Formidable Forms reports just like in the screenshot below.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169695\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidble-forms-reports-in-mi-dashboard-reports.jpg\" alt=\"formidble-forms-reports-in-mi-dashboard-reports\" width=\"620\" height=\"532\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidble-forms-reports-in-mi-dashboard-reports.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidble-forms-reports-in-mi-dashboard-reports-300x257.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The first column from the left is the list of your Formidable forms’ names. The second column is the number of impressions, and the third is the number of successful form submissions. The last column shows the conversion rate for your forms.</p>\n<p>It’s very simple and easy to understand!</p>\n<p>Now, if you want to view more details regarding your form conversions, you can click the <strong>View Full Forms Report</strong> button at the bottom of the report.</p>\n<p>Doing so will redirect you to <strong>Google Analytics » Behavior » Events » Top Events</strong> in your Google Analytics account. If you aren’t already logged in, you’ll need to log into your Google Analytics account to view this report.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169696\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-conversion-reports-ga.jpg\" alt=\"formidable-forms-conversion-reports-ga\" width=\"620\" height=\"486\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-conversion-reports-ga.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-conversion-reports-ga-300x235.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see above in the screenshot, it shows the total impressions and conversions triggered by all your forms.</p>\n<p>If you want to view the events for each form individually, click on <strong>Event Label</strong> link in your Forms report <strong>Primary Dimension</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169697\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-individual-form-reports-ga.jpg\" alt=\"formidable-forms-individual-form-reports-ga\" width=\"620\" height=\"570\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-individual-form-reports-ga.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/formidable-forms-individual-form-reports-ga-300x276.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you&#8217;ll see the total events for each of your Formidable Forms forms individually. Total events include both impressions and conversions for your forms.</p>\n<p>If you want to see impressions and conversions separately for each form, click your form names one-by-one.</p>\n<p>After doing that, here’s how the <strong>Impression</strong> and <strong>Conversion</strong> data are provided separately:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169698\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-formidable-forms-reports-for-each-form.jpg\" alt=\"view-formidable-forms-reports-for-each-form\" width=\"620\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-formidable-forms-reports-for-each-form.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-formidable-forms-reports-for-each-form-300x231.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to track your Formidable Forms conversions with Google Analytics. If you found MonsterInsights useful, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">download it today</a>!</p>\n<p>You may also want to see our detailed guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-real-time-reports-in-google-analytics/\">find real-time reports in Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-formidable-forms-conversions-with-google-analytics/\">How to Track Formidable Forms Conversions with Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-formidable-forms-conversions-with-google-analytics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"How to Add PayPal to Referral Exclusion List in Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:205:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 08 Nov 2018 16:03:33 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"referral exclusion list\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=169180\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:678:\"<p>Want to learn how to add PayPal to your referral exclusion list in Google Analytics? If you’re using PayPal to accept payments, Google Analytics will list PayPal as the referrer source instead of original referrer sites. This prevents you from seeing the original referrer websites contributing to your conversions. To prevent tracking PayPal as referrer [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics/\">How to Add PayPal to Referral Exclusion List in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7224:\"<p>Want to learn how to add PayPal to your referral exclusion list in Google Analytics? If you’re using PayPal to accept payments, Google Analytics will list PayPal as the referrer source instead of original referrer sites. This prevents you from seeing the original referrer websites contributing to your conversions.</p>\n<p>To prevent tracking PayPal as referrer and to track the real referrers, you need to add PayPal to the referral exclusion list in Google Analytics. And, here’s how to do that in just a few steps.</p>\n<h3>Why Google Analytics Lists PayPal as the Referrer – Explained</h3>\n<p>When using PayPal as your payment gateway, your customers leave your site and log into PayPal&#8217;s website to make a payment. After they pay successfully, they return to your site, often to a Thank You page, and the conversion is made.</p>\n<p>Essentially, Google Analytics tracks the last website visited before conversion as the referral source for that conversion. Hence, it attributes PayPal as the referral source for the transaction. But, in reality, the referral source is where the customer found your website or product link, not PayPal.</p>\n<p>For example, a customer comes to your site from an affiliate website and decides to buy a product. After adding the product to their cart, your site redirects the user to PayPal&#8217;s website to make the payment. Now, they log into PayPal, pay for the product, and return to your site. And that’s a conversion for your site.</p>\n<p>Now Google Analytics adds PayPal to referral traffic data because PayPal is the last site user visited before conversion. But the actual referral source is the affiliate website, not PayPal.</p>\n<p>In this way, PayPal takes the place of multiple referral source sites and prevents you from seeing the actual referrers. That’s why you should exclude PayPal or any other third-party payment gateway from your referral list. Here&#8217;s how to do that:</p>\n<h3>1. Finding Your eCommerce Referrals in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>Before adding PayPal to the Referral Exclusion List, it’s best to check how many users are listed as referred by PayPal.</p>\n<p>To view your eCommerce referral list, you’ll need to visit <strong>Acquisition » All Traffic » Referrals</strong> from your Google Analytics panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169255\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-referrals-ga-traffic.jpg\" alt=\"view-referrals-ga-traffic\" width=\"266\" height=\"584\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-referrals-ga-traffic.jpg 266w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/view-referrals-ga-traffic-137x300.jpg 137w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 266px) 100vw, 266px\" /></p>\n<p>Then click on <strong>eCommerce</strong> under the Explorer tab.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169256\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-list-ga.jpg\" alt=\"referral-list-ga\" width=\"620\" height=\"503\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-list-ga.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-list-ga-300x243.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As shown in the screenshot above, <strong>paypal.com</strong> made it to the top of the list. That’s because all the referral traffic coming from multiple sources uses PayPal to make payments.</p>\n<h3>2. Adding PayPal to Referral Exclusion List in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>To add PayPal to your referral exclusion list, you’ll need to click the <strong>Admin</strong> option at the bottom of the Analytics panel on the left.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169257\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ga-admin.jpg\" alt=\"ga-admin\" width=\"250\" height=\"586\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ga-admin.jpg 250w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ga-admin-128x300.jpg 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px\" /></p>\n<p>Navigate to <strong>Tracking Info</strong> option in the <strong>Property</strong> section. Then, select <strong>Referral Exclusion List</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169258\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-exclusion-list-ga.jpg\" alt=\"referral-exclusion-list-ga\" width=\"620\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-exclusion-list-ga.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/referral-exclusion-list-ga-300x220.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Upon clicking <strong>Referral Exclusion List</strong>, you’ll see your list of excluded sites.</p>\n<p>Now all you need to do is to add paypal.com to the list. To do so, click the <strong>Add Referral Exclusion</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169259\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-referral-exclusion.jpg\" alt=\"add-referral-exclusion\" width=\"620\" height=\"243\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-referral-exclusion.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-referral-exclusion-300x118.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, enter paypal.com to the domain box and click the <strong>Create</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169260\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-referral-exclusion-ga.jpg\" alt=\"create-referral-exclusion-ga\" width=\"523\" height=\"221\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-referral-exclusion-ga.jpg 523w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-referral-exclusion-ga-300x127.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 523px) 100vw, 523px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s it! Now you can see paypal.com on the list.</p>\n<p>Now that you’ve added PayPal to the referral exclusion list, Google Analytics will track the original referral sites and provide you with accurate referral traffic data.</p>\n<p>Google Analytics normally takes 24-48 hours to apply an exclusion. You can check your referral source data again after that time to check if the exclusion list is working for you.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to exclude PayPal from referral traffic data in Google Analytics. You may also want to learn <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-does-google-analytics-work-beginners-guide/\">how Google Analytics works</a>.</p>\n<p>Don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics/\">How to Add PayPal to Referral Exclusion List in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:102:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-paypal-to-referral-exclusion-list-in-google-analytics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"